    Scope and Contents
WWII CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTORS PROJECT
"Mr. W" (real name withheld), jailed for rejection of conscientious objector status for the WWII draft, discusses his Russian Jewish background, family beliefs and socialism, objections to the war, prison, volunteering for non-combatant service, and travel in the Middle East and France.1 tape, 75 mins., 22 pp.
Interview by C. Arthur Bradley, 1988
